        <div class="blog-article-body">

            <p class="blog-lead">
                Accountants and bookkeepers deal with more PDFs than almost any
                other profession — invoices, bank statements, tax forms, contracts,
                payroll documents. Here's the toolkit that saves the most time.
            </p>

            <h2>1. AI Invoice Data Extractor</h2>
            <p>
                The biggest time-saver for any accounting team. Instead of manually
                copying vendor names, amounts, and line items from invoice PDFs into
                your accounting software, AI reads every field and exports to Excel
                automatically.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>Best for:</strong> Accounts payable teams, bookkeepers
                processing supplier invoices, anyone doing monthly reconciliation.
            </p>
            <p>
                <a href="/extract-invoice-data">Try Invoice Data Extractor →</a>
            </p>

            <h2>2. PDF Compressor</h2>
            <p>
                Bank statements, financial reports, and annual accounts are often
                huge PDFs. When you need to email them to clients or upload to
                a portal with file size limits, compression is essential.
                A good compressor reduces file size by 60-80% without making
                text blurry or unreadable.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>Best for:</strong> Sending financial statements to clients,
                uploading to HMRC/IRS portals, archiving large report PDFs.
            </p>
            <p>
                <a href="/compress-pdf">Try PDF Compressor →</a>
            </p>

            <h2>3. PDF Merger</h2>
            <p>
                Quarterly reports often come as separate monthly files.
                Client files span multiple documents. Merge PDFs combines them
                into one organized document — drag to reorder pages before merging.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>Best for:</strong> Combining monthly statements into
                quarterly reports, consolidating client documents, creating
                audit packages.
            </p>
            <p>
                <a href="/merge-pdf">Try PDF Merger →</a>
            </p>

            <h2>4. PDF Password Protection</h2>
            <p>
                Financial documents contain sensitive data. Adding password
                protection before emailing payroll documents, tax returns,
                or financial statements is a basic security practice that
                every accounting firm should follow.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>Best for:</strong> Emailing payroll documents,
                sending tax returns to clients, protecting sensitive
                financial reports.
            </p>
            <p>
                <a href="/lock-pdf">Try Lock PDF →</a>
            </p>

            <h2>5. PDF Redaction Tool</h2>
            <p>
                Sometimes you need to share a document but hide certain
                figures — bank account numbers, personal identifiers, or
                commercially sensitive amounts. Redaction permanently removes
                text so it can't be recovered, unlike covering it with a
                black box in a viewer.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>Best for:</strong> Removing sensitive data before
                sharing documents externally, preparing documents for audits,
                GDPR compliance.
            </p>
            <p>
                <a href="/redact-pdf">Try PDF Redaction →</a>
            </p>

            <h2>6. Batch Processing</h2>
            <p>
                When you have 20 invoices to compress, or 15 statements to
                protect with a password, doing them one at a time is painful.
                Batch processing lets you upload multiple files, apply a tool
                to all of them, and download the results as a ZIP.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>Best for:</strong> End-of-month processing,
                bulk document preparation, archive management.
            </p>
            <p>
                <a href="/batch">Try Batch Processing →</a>
            </p>

            <h2>7. PDF OCR (for scanned documents)</h2>
            <p>
                Older invoices, receipts, and paper documents that have been
                scanned are image-based PDFs — you can't search or copy the text.
                OCR adds a searchable text layer where recognition succeeds and enables AI extraction.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>Best for:</strong> Processing legacy paper documents,
                making scanned receipts searchable, preparing old invoices
                for digital archiving.
            </p>
            <p>
                <a href="/pdf-ocr">Try PDF OCR →</a>
            </p>

            <h2>What to look for in a PDF tool</h2>
            <p>
                For accounting work specifically, the most important factors are:
                privacy (files should be deleted after processing, never stored
                permanently), accuracy (especially for AI extraction tools),
                and batch capability (doing one file at a time doesn't scale).
                PdfToolStack deletes all files within 1 hour and never trains
                AI models on your documents.
            </p>

